Good tips, however it&#x27;s still often beneficial to do reciprocal float division: i.e.<p><pre><code>  float rcpDiv = 1.0f / value;
  float finalValue = myValue * rcpDiv;
</code></pre>
In a lot of cases when speed matters. With fpmath=fast, I&#x27;ve seen compilers do that for you, but not always, as it potentially changes the answer very slightly.
